                <h1>Unraveling "The Yellow Wallpaper": A Study of Mental Illness</h1>
                <p>The Yellow Wallpaper, a short story by Charlotte Perkins Gilman, explores themes of mental illness and the oppression of women in the 19th century. The protagonist's descent into madness reflects the damaging effects of societal expectations and isolation. The wallpaper symbolizes her struggle for freedom and identity.</p>
